Action: Since the intersseous muscles cross on the metatarsophalangeal joint then they act on that specific joint and cause adduction of toes III IV and V.[1] Adduction itself is not of extreme importance to the toes but these muscles work together with the dorsal interosseous muscles in flexion of the foot. They also work together to strengthen the metatarsal arch.[2]
